Cosmos Corp., maker of TropiClean and Naturel Promise pet grooming products, is expanding with a $26 million headquarters facility in O’Fallon, Mo.The new 240,000-square-foot facility on 25 acres at 521 Pearl Drive will house the company’s administration, manufacturing and distribution operations. An affiliated nonprofit, Gifts of Love, will also be based at the new facility.

“We appreciate the excellent business climate and workforce that the state and St. Louis area has to offer and look forward to bringing even more jobs to the region,” Cosmos CEO Landon Hobson said in a statement announcing the expansion.
Wentzville-based Cosmos has had a presence in Missouri since 1989 and employs more than 100 people locally. With the expansion, the company plans to add 60 full-time jobs by early 2020, when construction is completed. The company is eligible to receive up to $50,700 in tax exemption incentives and $893,844 from the state’s Missouri Works program, according to Missouri Department of Economic Development officials.
“We are honored that they chose to continue growing and basing their operations here in Missouri,” Gov. Mike Parson said in the statement.


