High honors came to Chief Frank Mininni of the Normandy Police Department, who earned an award from Missouri Gov. Mike Parson.The honor lauds higher ranking officers who have improved safety and cooperation by trying to reduce the gulf that often exists between police and residents.

Mininni, who became head of the Normandy department 22 years after joining the force, started a community engagement program in the city involving patrol officers, and also created a lunch program in which officers eat lunch at local schools and talk to students.
In 2015, the department got an $800,000 federal grant to put school resource officers back into Normandy schools.
Mininni was awarded the Director's Leadership Medal by Parson at a ceremony Monday at Harris-Stowe State University.


