Updated 12:00 a.m. With almost all votes counted, Missouri appears to have overwhelmingly approved a plan to gradually raise the state's current $7.85 minimum wage.Proposition B will bump the minimum rate to $8.60 an hour starting Jan. 1, and increase it every year by 85 cents until reaching $12 in 2023.

