WASHINGTON  •  Here's a look at some of the statements by area members of Congress and other elected officials about the passing of U.S. Sen. John McCain, who died Saturday:Sen. Roy Blunt, R-Mo.: “As I served with John McCain he became one of my heroes. We didn’t always agree but he was always motivated to do what he thought was the right thing.”U.S. Sen. Claire McCaskill, D-Mo. (via Twitter): “I feel so fortunate that I had a chance to learn from him and laugh with him. He was a tremendous role model for our democracy and gave his life to the public good. My love to the McCain family. There’ll never be another like John McCain.”

U.S. Sen. Dick Durbin, D-Ill. (via Twitter): “My friend and America’s hero, John McCain, landed safely tonight at Heaven’s gates.”Rep. Blaine Luetkemeyer, R-Mo.: “Today, the world has lost a great American hero. Senator John McCain served our nation for more than half a century, dedicating his life as a distinguished member of the United States Navy and the United States Senate. Please join me in keeping his wife Cindy and his loving family in your thoughts and prayers this evening.”Rep. Mike Bost, R-Ill. (via Twitter): “Tracy and I send our prayers to the McCain family during this very difficult time. Senator McCain, you will be truly missed.”
Rep. John Shimkus, R-Ill. “Senator John McCain devoted his life to the country he loved and served as the very model of a warrior and statesman. The legacy of his many decades of public service left no question that he unapologetically put country first. My thoughts and prayers are with his family, loved ones, and our nation that now mourns his passing.”U.S. Sen. Tammy Duckworth, D-Ill.: “My heart is heavy today as I join countless Americans across our country in mourning the loss of one of our nation’s greatest leaders and statesmen, one of my personal heroes, Senator John McCain. Throughout his life — as a naval aviator, a prisoner of war who endured years of torture, a congressman, and a six-term senator — John repeatedly showed how anything is possible when armed with determination, a deep sense of patriotism and an unbreakable will.”
Other elected officials:Missouri Gov. Mike Parson (via Twitter): “Saddened to hear about the passing of a great veteran and public servant Senator John McCain. Our prayers are with his family.”Missouri Attorney General Josh Hawley (via Twitter): “America has lost a great man and war hero. Sen. John McCain and his family are in our thoughts and prayers.”Illinois Gov. Bruce Rauner (via Twitter): “It’s heartbreaking to hear the latest news from Senator John McCain. He’s a true American hero and a patriot.”


