JEFFERSON CITY • Gov. Mike Parson returned to Missouri Wednesday after attending a political conference in Colorado.The two-day event in Aspen marked Parson’s first meeting with the Republican Governor’s Association, which heavily bankrolled his scandal-plagued predecessor’s election in 2016.At the event, the organization held panels and briefings on this year’s 36 gubernatorial elections and about how GOP governors are trying to create jobs in their states.

Other governors on hand for the meetings were Wisconsin Gov. Scott Walker, Texas Gov. Greg Abbott and Tennessee Gov. Bill Haslam.Since taking office, Parson also has visited Washington, where he met with President Donald Trump.• Before you vote in the Missouri primary, learn the candidates and issues
Parson took over as governor June 1 after Gov. Eric Greitens quit amid multiple scandals, including possible federal and state fundraising violations connected to principles associated with the RGA.Michael Adams, who is general counsel for the RGA, was the attorney involved in the filing of an allegedly falsified settlement agreement with the Missouri Ethics Commission in connection with a Greitens fundraising violation. His tenure as the organization’s top attorney overlapped with Vice President Mike Pence’s chief of staff Nick Ayers’ role as executive director of the RGA.
While advising Greitens during his campaign, Ayers discussed soliciting contributions from “restricted donors,”  according to a complaint filed earlier this month with the state’s ethics commission.In his first year in office, Greitens went on at least four out-of-state trips related to his role in the Republican Governors Association, which funneled $13 million into his successful general election campaign against Attorney General Chris Koster, a Democrat.Greitens flew to Florida for an RGA-sponsored conference in Miami at Trump National Doral golf course. He attended another RGA event in Colorado and went to Nashville for a series of meetings.Greitens left for an RGA event in Texas just two days after returning from a weeklong trip to Israel.


