JEFFERSON CITY • With significant questions still looming over the status of investigations into soon-to-resign Gov. Eric Greitens, legislative leaders turned their attention Wednesday to helping guide Lt. Gov. Mike Parson’s transition into the top spot in Missouri government.A day after the scandal-plagued Greitens announced he would resign effective 5 p.m. Friday, Parson spent Wednesday in meetings and phone calls discussing his imminent elevation to governor, spokeswoman Kelli Jones said.Jones said Parson would be sworn in as Missouri’s 57th governor immediately after 5 p.m. Friday. A judge has not been chosen for the ceremony, she added.



